  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 9 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 2 critical, 12 high, 14 medium, 11 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR); plus 11 other bases. 14 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, mist and low cloud base  — most notably around Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD), Budapest Liszt Ferenc (BUD/LHBP) and London Luton (LTN/EGGW). Network hotspots: Billund (BLL/EKBI), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD), Plovdiv (PDV/LBPD), Lyon Saint-Exupéry (LYS/LFLL), Budapest Liszt Ferenc (BUD/LHBP) and 4 others. Primary drivers: snow / blowing snow, low cloud base and mist. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Billund (BLL/EKBI), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD), Plovdiv (PDV/LBPD) and 9 others.",
